---
import {
  Apple,
  Coins,
  DatabaseZap,
  HouseHeart,
  MapPinHouse,
  Siren,
} from "@lucide/astro";
import Blurb from "../components/blurb.astro";
import Footer from "../components/footer.astro";
import Input from "../components/input.astro";
import Issue from "../components/issue.astro";
import Textarea from "../components/textarea.astro";
import Default from "../layouts/default.astro";
---

<Default>
  <main class="p-8 md:p-16 pb-0! flex flex-col gap-32">
    <section class="w-full flex flex-wrap justify-center items-center gap-8">
      <div class="w-md">
        <h1>I'm running for Denver City Council At Large</h1>
        <p>
          Because Denver can be <strong
            >the community we've always wanted,</strong
          > or it can be a playground for corporate interests.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary mt-8" href="/#get-involved">Get involved</a>
      </div>
      <img
        src="/assets/lake2.jpg"
        alt="Photo of Gabriel"
        class="w-full max-w-md"
      />
    </section>
    <section
      id="issues"
      class="w-[calc(100% + 2rem)] bg-secondary px-8 md:px-16 py-32 -mx-8 md:-mx-16 text-white"
    >
      <h1 class="text-center mb-16!">What will I tackle?</h1>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-16 justify-center">
        <Issue Icon={Coins} title="Affordability"
          >Average rent in Denver increased by 45% over the past 10 years. Gas
          increased by 100%. Food by 44%. Have your wages kept up? Workers'
          rights are repeatedly curtailed, while corporations get hall passes.
          Denver must be a city for all, not the 1%.<br /><br /><a
            class="link"
            href="/issues/affordability">Read More</a
          ></Issue
        >
        <Issue Icon={MapPinHouse} title="Housing Crisis"
          >Companies from California and China buying up neighborhood homes only
          to flip them/charge exorbitant rents or building giant, luxury
          apartment high-rises benefits no one but California and China. Solving
          the Denver housing crisis starts with Denver ownership.<br /><br /><a
            class="link"
            href="/issues/housing-crisis">Read More</a
          ></Issue
        >
        <Issue Icon={Siren} title="Criminal Injustice"
          >Most people end up in jail for low-level, non-violent crimes, leading
          to an intentional pipeline of vulnerable people being funneled to
          for-profit prison systems that implement modern day slavery in
          Colorado. These racist and ableist systems must be circumvented.<br
          /><br /><a class="link" href="/issues/criminal-injustice">Read More</a
          ></Issue
        >
        <Issue Icon={Apple} title="Food Security"
          >As someone who skipped meals because I couldn't afford food, eating
          ice to feel full, I know firsthand how important food security is to
          health and mental well-being. We deserve healthy food for all
          Denverites.<br /><br /><a class="link" href="/issues/food-security"
            >Read More</a
          >
        </Issue>
        <Issue Icon={HouseHeart} title="Homelessness"
          >Since my early twenties, I've worked with our neighbors experiencing
          homelessness. It's time to set aside the misconceptions and
          unjustified fears. Housing-first policies work. Let's put a roof over
          every Denverite's head.<br /><br /><a
            class="link"
            href="/issues/homelessness">Read More</a
          ></Issue
        >
        <Issue Icon={DatabaseZap} title="Big Tech"
          >Big tech will not save us. They're not even <em>trying</em> to save us.
          They're trying to make money off of us. The sooner we realize this, the
          sooner we can push back against their schemes to use Denver as a foothold
          for surveillance, data centers, and cheap labor.<br /><br /><a
            class="link"
            href="/issues/big-tech">Read More</a
          ></Issue
        >
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="why-me">
      <h1 class="text-center mb-16!">Why me?</h1>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-16">
        <Blurb title="I'm a community organizer."
          >I've been the head cook for a charity kitchen, started a mutual aid
          and political action group, served on the board of a non-profit
          providing food security to those in need during COVID, organized
          concerts, advocated for local filmmaking, spoke at local meetups
          across the state, and am the Lay Leader at Cameron Church on Pearl
          Street. Serving on City Council will be the culmination of my
          endeavours, and the best way I can continue to advocate for you.</Blurb
        >
        <Blurb title="I'm a jack of all trades. Literally."
          >From managing a fast food chain, to working in finance, to cleaning
          restaurants overnight, to making local TV commercials, to electrician
          work, to driving schoolbuses, to working in tech, it sometimes feels
          like there's not a job I haven't done, yet. Who better to represent
          you than someone who's been in the trenches with you?</Blurb
        >
        <Blurb title="I'm no stranger to poverty."
          >I grew up on a rural farm. We ate what we grew. We went to clothing
          swaps. We patched those same clothes when they wore holes. And Wendy's
          was fine dining to us. I wouldn't trade that childhood for anything.
          Since growing up, I've experienced the thick and the thin, from living
          out of my car and eating ice to feel full to owning my own home. Your
          city leadership should know what it's like to be on both sides of the
          poverty line.</Blurb
        >
      </div>
    </section>
    <section
      id="get-involved"
      class="w-[calc(100% + 2rem)] bg-primary px-8 md:px-16 py-32 -mx-8 md:-mx-16 text-white"
    >
      <h1 class="text-center mb-16!">Get involved</h1>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-16">
        <form
          class="w-xs flex flex-col items-end text-black!"
          action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit"
          method="POST"
        >
          <input
            type="hidden"
            name="access_key"
            value="a5af05ef-33e3-424d-b4bd-2f900039335b"
          />
          <Input name="name" label="Name" placeholder="Jane Doe" required />
          <Input
            type="email"
            name="email"
            label="Email"
            placeholder="jane.doe@gmail.com"
            required
          />
          <Textarea
            name="message"
            label="Message"
            placeholder="So, I wanted to ask..."
            required
          />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-accent mt-4">Send</button>
        </form>
        <Blurb title="Start the conversation."
          >Send me a message. I'll respond. Personally. If you have more
          questions about my plans, who I am, or how you can help, don't leave
          yourself guessing. Just ask!</Blurb
        >
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Default>
